  "doc_id": "34966",
  "text": "The increased degradation of translation products in mrpl36⌬C mitochondria could be due to defects in their structure. We reasoned that combination of this mutation with mutations that reduce accuracy of translation might further impair respiratory competence of mrpl36⌬C cells. To this end, we analyzed whether the CE domain of Mrpl36 interacts genetically with Guf1, the mitochondrial homologue of bacterial LepA [CITATION_1] . LepA is a factor that mediates the back translocation of the ribosome to prevent amino acid misincorporation [CITATION_2] . Conversely, presence of LepA in an in vitro translation assay increases accuracy [CITATION_3] . Cells deficient in either Guf1 or the CE domain of Mrpl36 could grow on a nonfermentable carbon source. In contrast, the combination of both deletions inhibited respiratory growth completely ( Figure 6A ).",
